  "texts": [
    "Commonly, a zoo of DNNs is generated using a collection of static DNN models that have a fixed computational graph and parameters during inference (often referred to as the bag-of-models approach).",
    "Alternatively, we can employ a single dynamic DNN that has a dynamic computational graph that enables partial execution and virtually embeds multiple DNN variants in one base DNN.",
    "Each of these strategies has its advantages and disadvantages.",
    "We can easily construct static DNN variants by downloading different pretrained models or by training different Fig.",
    "architectures separately with standard methodologies."
  ],
